overview: The user initiated a request to enhance the aesthetic appeal of their
  sleep questionnaire application, which they felt was visually lacking. The
  agent conducted a thorough review of the existing design, identifying areas
  for improvement in color palette, typography, spacing, form elements, and
  overall visual interest. A new, calming sleep-themed color palette was
  introduced, along with custom utility classes for gradients and shadows. The
  main form layout was redesigned with decorative background elements and an
  improved progress indicator. Key UI components like checkboxes, radio buttons,
  sliders, and cards were polished with updated styling and interactive states.
  The intro section was transformed into a more engaging welcome experience with
  feature cards and refined alerts. All questionnaire sections were updated to
  use consistent, visually appealing card-style groupings. Additionally, a
  console error related to null input values was identified and fixed by
  modifying the Input component to safely handle  values. The outcome is a
  significantly more polished, cohesive, and professional-looking sleep health
  application.
